9. De tribus bonorum generibus, scilicet, fortune, nature, et gracie. This is the common classification; the goods of nature are those which are intrinsic to the body ; the goods of fortune are exte-mal events which affect it in any way; while the goods of grace are those which concern man's spiritual nature. Elsewhere Wycliffe has a more minute sub- division distributing the three ‘goods' into five classes: De civili Do- minio i. 13 pp. 88 seqq.
